{"type":"route","meta":{"status":200,"headers":{"content-type":"text/markdown","x-next-cache-tags":"_N_T_/layout,_N_T_/llms.mdx/layout,_N_T_/llms.mdx/docs/layout,_N_T_/llms.mdx/docs/[[...slug]]/layout,_N_T_/llms.mdx/docs/[[...slug]]/route,_N_T_/llms.mdx/docs/reporting/content.md"}},"body":"# Reporting & Analytics (/docs/reporting)\n\n\n\nThe Reports section gives you a deeper look at your salon's performance beyond the day-to-day. All reports are filterable, exportable, and organised by category so you can find what you need quickly.\n\nClick **Reports** in the left menu to get started.\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n  Reports are only accessible to admin users.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nFinding a report [#finding-a-report]\n\nThe main reports page shows all available reports as cards. You can:\n\n* **Search** by report name or description\n* **Filter by creator** using the All creators dropdown\n* **Filter by type** using the All reports dropdown\n* **Browse by category** using the tabs across the top: All reports · Sales · Finance · Appointments · Team · Clients · Inventory\n\nThe left sidebar organises reports into:\n\n| Category    | What's in it                                         |\n| ----------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |\n| All reports | Every report in one place                            |\n| Favourites  | Reports you've starred for quick access              |\n| Dashboards  | Visual overview reports (e.g. Performance dashboard) |\n| Premium     | Premium-tier reports                                 |\n| Folders     | Custom folders you create to organise reports        |\n\nStar any report card to add it to your **Favourites**.\n\n***\n\nAvailable reports [#available-reports]\n\nPerformance Dashboard [#performance-dashboard]\n\n*(Dashboards)*\n\nA visual overview of your salon's performance. Shows key metrics, charts, and trends across revenue, appointments, services, and staff — all in one place.\n\n***\n\nSales Log [#sales-log]\n\n*(Sales)*\n\nA detailed record of every sale — including the services sold, discounts applied, payment methods used, staff member, and client. Use this when you need to trace a specific transaction or review sales over a period.\n\n**Filters:** Date range, location, team member, client, payment method.\n\n**Export:** CSV, Excel, PDF.\n\n***\n\nFinance Summary [#finance-summary]\n\n*(Finance)*\n\nA period-by-period breakdown of your sales, payments, and liabilities. Perfect for month-end reviews and accounting.\n\nChoose how to group the data:\n\n| Period  | What you'll see                  |\n| ------- | -------------------------------- |\n| Day     | Last 30 days, one column per day |\n| Week    | Last 4 weeks                     |\n| Month   | Last 6 months (default)          |\n| Quarter | Last 4 quarters                  |\n| Year    | Last 3 years                     |\n\n**Export:** CSV, Excel, PDF.\n\n***\n\nPayment Transactions [#payment-transactions]\n\n*(Finance)*\n\nA full log of every individual payment collected. Use this to verify payment method totals or trace a specific transaction.\n\n**Filters:** Date range, location, team member, payment method, transaction type, amount range.\n\n**Export:** CSV, Excel, PDF.\n\n***\n\nTips Summary [#tips-summary]\n\n*(Team)*\n\nAn overview of all tips received, broken down by staff member. Shows total tips, number of tipped transactions, average tip, and tip percentage for each person.\n\n**Filters:** Date range, location, team member, payment method.\n\n**Export:** CSV, Excel, PDF.\n\n***\n\nExport options [#export-options]\n\nAll reports can be exported in:\n\n| Format        | Best for                                |\n| ------------- | --------------------------------------- |\n| CSV           | Importing into a spreadsheet            |\n| Excel (.xlsx) | A formatted, ready-to-share spreadsheet |\n| PDF           | Printing or sharing outside the system  |\n\n***\n\nDate range options [#date-range-options]\n\nAll reports use the same date picker with quick presets:\n\n* Today / Yesterday\n* Last 7, 30, or 90 days\n* Last week / Last month / Last 3, 6, or 12 months\n* Week-to-date / Month-to-date / Quarter-to-date / Year-to-date\n* Custom start and end date\n"}